---

Vision

LokSetu is an open, citizen-centric platform that organizes officially published information about public offices, elected representatives, public services, official contact channels, and grievance mechanisms across India.

The objective is to make it easier for every citizen to identify:

- Which public office is responsible for a service.
- How to contact that office through officially published channels.
- Which authority to approach if a grievance is not resolved.
- Where the official information originated.

LokSetu is built using only officially published public information from authentic government sources.

---

Project Objectives

- Build a nationwide directory of public offices.
- Publish only officially available public contact information.
- Organize government administrative structures.
- Map public services to responsible offices.
- Display official grievance escalation mechanisms.
- Maintain complete source attribution and audit history.
- Support multilingual access.
- Provide open APIs for civic innovation.

---

Guiding Principles

Office First

LokSetu models public offices, not individuals.

Office holders may change over time, but the office remains the permanent civic entity.

---

Official Sources Only

Every published record must originate from an official public source, such as:

- Government websites
- Official department directories
- Gazette notifications
- RTI proactive disclosures
- Official helpline publications

---

Complete Traceability

Every published field can be traced back to:

- Source
- Publication
- Verification
- Last review

---

Open by Default

Verified public information should be openly accessible to every citizen.

---

Karnataka MVP Scope

The first public release covers Karnataka.

Initial departments include:

- Revenue Department
- Forest Department
- Excise Department
- Health Department
- Education Department
- Public-facing offices of the Home Department
- State and district helplines
- Emergency services
- Elected representatives (from Gram Panchayat to the President of India)

Sensitive operational or non-public entities are outside the scope.

